                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.AD1/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vincent</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-18T10:00:00+07:00"
                            >March 18, 1943—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:21 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>389. With reference to Department’s 310, March 8, 9 p.m.<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d731fn5">See footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_820">p. 820</ref>.</note>
                    Acting Minister of Foreign Affairs<note n="6" xml:id="d731fn6">K. C. Wu.</note>
                    has informed me orally that the Chinese Government accepts the invitation to the
                    proposed conference and that such suggestions and comments as it may have to
                    make will be communicated separately on a subsequent date or be incorporated in
                    the instructions of the delegates for communication when they arrive in
                    Washington. Unofficially he stated that the delegation would probably be
                    composed of seven or eight men and that every effort would be made to have them
                    arrive in Washington by April 27, April 5 having been set as the deadline for
                    preparation for their departure from Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Vincent</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
